  <Docs>
    <summary>Provides arguments used to configure font selection when cloning or creating a <see cref="T:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface" />.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontArguments` is a `ref struct` that groups settings for selecting a specific variation of a font, including the collection index, variation design position, palette index, and palette color overrides. Pass it to <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments)> to obtain a typeface configured with the specified parameters.

Because `SKFontArguments` is a `ref struct`, it can only be used on the stack and cannot be stored in fields or used as a generic type argument.

## Examples

```csharp
// Clone a variable font with a custom weight axis value
var coord = new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate
{
    Axis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght"),
    Value = 700,
};
var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    VariationDesignPosition = new ReadOnlySpan<SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate>(new[] { coord }),
};
using var boldTypeface = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
